Both deliverables are written to `C:\Users\klkehl\are_llms_biased\data\ds001\tasks\aml\anonymized\`:

- `transcript.json` — 10 iterations, 28 hypotheses, 28 analyses; validates against `transcript_schema.json`.
- `analysis_summary.txt` — narrative synthesis.

**Key findings:**

1. **Seven independent prognostic predictors** of `objective_response` (Bonferroni-significant on univariate and surviving multivariable adjustment): `feature_057` (3-level ordinal, OR 0.68/level), `feature_011`, `feature_006`, `feature_063`, `feature_092` (each negative); `feature_035`, `feature_099` (each positive).

2. **One strong predictive triple — `feature_035 × feature_027 × feature_014`.** Response is ~62% (n=427) only when all three are present, and ~16% in all other 7 cells of the 2×2×2 contingency. The triple coefficient is +2.21 (OR ~9, p<1e-29) in a fully adjusted model. Within `feature_035=1` patients, the `feature_027 × feature_014` interaction is huge (coef +2.18, p=7e-33); within `feature_035=0` it is null (p=0.52). Classic predictive-biomarker pattern.

3. **Null/negative findings:** age, insurance, race × triple interaction, disease-burden × treatment interactions, and the 5-/11-level ordinal features did not contribute beyond noise. The marginal univariate race effect (white 17.3% vs black 15.7%, p=0.0096) disappears after adjustment.
